<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="393" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,901,1072]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,937,963]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">Distribution.</emphasis>
Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S." box="[492,828,937,963]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" pagination="273 - 292" refId="ref18519" refString="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S. (2003) Biogeography of benthic marine amphipods in Mediterranean Sea. Biogeographia-The Journal of Integrative Biogeography, 24 (1), 273 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.21426 / B 6110176" type="journal article" year="2003">Bellan-Santini &amp; Ruffo 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The species is reported in 
<collectingCountry box="[1147,1228,937,963]" name="Cyprus" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
(Vasiliko bay) for the first time. In Vasiliko Bay, it is considered as a rare species (FI: 2.38 %).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="393" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,901,1072]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,252,1009,1035]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">Ecology.</emphasis>
In Vasiliko Bay it was found at 
<quantity box="[606,648,1009,1036]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" unit="m" value="6.0">6 m</quantity>
depth, in sandy substrate with 2.364 % organic matter. The station was in “high” ecological status according to the Bentix Index.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
